strategies.intervention:
1) Promote green building concepts to mitigate urban heat risk • Promote energy efficient and green buildings • Transition to clean renewable energy sources to meet energy demand;
2) Enable non-motorized movement of people and promote shift to public transport • Accelerate transition to electric mobility powered by renewables • Strengthen management of traffic and decongest roads;
3) Reform policy and regulatory frameworks for water resilience • Provide efficient, equitable and safe access to water • Protect and revitalize urban lakes • Ecological restoration of Sabarmati riverfront • Efficient water supply networks powered by clean renewable energy; 
4) 100% efficient sewage collection and treatment •  Achieve 100% sludge and septage management • Adopt low carbon technology and improve operational and energy performance of wastewater management systems;
5) Adopt green city planning approaches to minimize runoff and urban flooding • Improve stormwater management and rehabilitate natural drains;
6) Minimize solid waste generation and maximize reuse and recycling • Ensure 100% source segregation and implement effective primary and secondary waste collection • Augment sustainable waste processing and disposal infrastructure;
7) Increase urban green cover using native plantation • Develop micro habitats for local biodiversity management • Increase carbon sink through urban greening;
8)Adopt measures to reduce vehicular air pollution • Manage construction activities and debris • Reduce air pollution from industrial activities

